

Android 9 (API level 28) >=
  -higher and use foreground services must request the FOREGROUND_SERVICE
  if not system throws a SecurityException.

Android 10 (API level 29) or higher
  accesses location information in a foreground service,
  declare the location foreground service type as an attribute of your <service> component.

Android 11 (API level 30) or higher
  accesses the camera or microphone in a foreground service,
  declare the camera or microphone foreground service types,
  respectively, as attributes of your <service> component.

  -Unless the user has granted the ACCESS_BACKGROUND_LOCATION permission to your app,
  the foreground service cannot access location.
  The foreground service cannot access the microphone or camera.